The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport

 Friday, October 01, 2004 

 IN THE CITY

 Shivika Burman reached the finals of both the ladies singles and girls under-18 singles categories of Aarbur Calcutta hard court tennis championship at Calcutta South Club on Thursday. In the both the events she had the same opponent, Treta Bhattacharyya. In the Ladies singles, she defeated Treta 6-1, 6-4 while in the U-18 she won 6-1, 6-1. Nirvick Mohinta made the finals of the boys U-18 defeating Sabyasachi Bose 6-4, 6-0. 

 Aloke Mukherjee, in a letter to IFA, has expressed his inability to join the Indian team?s camp as well as the Bengal camp for Santosh Trophy citing his wife?s illness. He has been named the assistant coach for India team and coach of the Bengal team. 

